trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of application-specific <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"></xref> instances used in combination with <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Representa uma coleção de específicas do aplicativo <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"> </xref> instâncias usadas em combinação com <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The PackageStore defines a reference collections of package that are open and active in the application.
trans-unit.target: PackageStore define uma coleção de referência do pacote está aberto e ativo no aplicativo.

trans-unit.source: Packages added to the PackageStore are accessed is by their key URI value.
trans-unit.target: Pacotes adicionados ao PackageStore são acessados é por seus valores URI de chave.

trans-unit.source: The PackageStore supports three common uses: 1.
trans-unit.target: PackageStore dá suporte a três usos comuns: 1.

trans-unit.source: Accessing <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> data through <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.
trans-unit.target: Acesso a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>dados por meio de <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>

trans-unit.source: The application obtaining an instance of a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package> given the package's URI.
trans-unit.target: O aplicativo obter uma instância de um <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>fornecido URI do pacote.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>

trans-unit.source: Accessing packages that are created and stored in a <xref:System.IO.MemoryStream>.
trans-unit.target: Acessar pacotes que são criados e armazenados em <xref:System.IO.MemoryStream>.</xref:System.IO.MemoryStream>

trans-unit.source: To improve performance and minimize the overhead of repeated file open/close operations, the PackageStore is used to manage instances of packages accessed by <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> and directly by the application.
trans-unit.target: Para melhorar o desempenho e minimizar a sobrecarga de operações de abrir e fechar arquivo repetidas, PackageStore é usado para gerenciar instâncias de pacotes acessados por <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>e diretamente pelo aplicativo.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>

trans-unit.source: When accessing data in a package, the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package> address of a requested <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> is first checked to see if the package is already defined and open in the PackageStore.
trans-unit.target: Ao acessar dados em um pacote, o <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>endereço de um solicitado <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>é verificado para ver se o pacote já está definido e aberto no PackageStore.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package>

trans-unit.source: If the package is defined as open in the PackageStore, requested parts can be accessed directly without repeatedly opening and closing the package for each request.
trans-unit.target: Se o pacote é definido como aberta no PackageStore, solicitadas partes podem ser acessados diretamente sem repetidamente abrir e fechar o pacote para cada solicitação.

trans-unit.source: If your application opens a package with <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Open%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> can be called to add the package to the PackageStore.
trans-unit.target: Se seu aplicativo abre um pacote com <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Open%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A>pode ser chamado para adicionar o pacote para PackageStore.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Open%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A> should later be called to remove the package from the PackageStore prior to calling <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Close%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A>mais tarde deve ser chamado para remover o pacote do PackageStore antes de chamar <xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Close%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.Package.Close%2A?displayProperty=fullName></xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A>

trans-unit.source: XPS packages opened with an <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A> constructor are automatically added and removed from the PackageStore when the document is created and disposed.
trans-unit.target: Pacotes XPS aberto com um <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A>construtor são automaticamente adicionados e removidos do PackageStore quando o documento é criado e descartado.</xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A>

trans-unit.source: (You do not need to call <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> or <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A> separately for XPS packages opened with <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A> constructors.) The file I/O permissions of a package accessed through the PackageStore remains the same as the I/O permissions set on the package when it is opened.
trans-unit.target: (Você não precisa chamar <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A>ou <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A>separadamente para pacotes XPS abertos com <xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A>construtores.)</xref:System.Windows.Xps.Packaging.XpsDocument.%23ctor%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.RemovePackage%2A> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore.AddPackage%2A> As permissões de e/s de arquivo de um pacote acessados por meio de PackageStore permanece o mesmo que as permissões de e/s definidos no pacote quando ele é aberto.

trans-unit.source: The PackageStore only provides references to the packages that have been added the store.
trans-unit.target: PackageStore só fornece referências para os pacotes que foram adicionados a loja.

trans-unit.source: It is up to the application to correctly open, update, and close each package.
trans-unit.target: É responsabilidade do aplicativo para abrir, atualizar e fechar cada pacote corretamente.

trans-unit.source: Packages added to the PackageStore can be accessed in multithreaded environments when they are used in combination with a [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] parser such as <xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Pacotes adicionados ao PackageStore podem ser acessados em ambientes multithread quando eles são usados em combinação com um [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] analisador como <xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: When operating in a multithreaded environment, the application must lock the package before access.
trans-unit.target: Ao operar em um ambiente multithreaded, o aplicativo deve bloquear o pacote antes de acesso.

trans-unit.source: Adds a <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"></xref> to the store.
trans-unit.target: Adiciona um <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.Package"> </xref> no repositório.

trans-unit.source: `packageUri` defines the package's key URI that is compared when you call <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.
trans-unit.target: `packageUri`Define a chave do pacote URI que é comparado ao chamar <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>

trans-unit.source: If the `packageUri` matches the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> for a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> in a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> call, the package defined in the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore> is used to access the requested part.
trans-unit.target: Se o `packageUri` corresponde a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>uma <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>em uma <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>chamada, o pacote definido no que <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore>é usada para acessar a parte de solicitada.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageStore> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the `packageUri` does not match the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A> for a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> in a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> call, the package with the specified URI is opened to access the requested part.
trans-unit.target: Se o `packageUri` não corresponde a <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>um <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart>em uma <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest>chamada, o pacote com o URI especificado é aberta para acessar a parte de solicitada.</xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackWebRequest> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart> </xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri%2A>
